#: src/fsearch_cli.c:181
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch --cli [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Search the existing FSearch index and print matching paths.\n"
"\n"
"  -s, --search PATTERN       Search with FSearch query syntax\n"
"      --path DIRECTORY        Search recursively below DIRECTORY (default: "
"current directory)\n"
"      --global                Search every indexed location\n"
"      --limit COUNT          Print at most COUNT results\n"
"      --unlimit, --unlimited Print every result\n"
"  -u, --update-database      Rescan the configured index and exit\n"
"      --about                Print one-line build information\n"
"  -h, --help                 Show this help\n"
"\n"
"Configuration: fsearch config --help\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search invoice              # current directory\n"
"  fsearch --cli --path ~/Documents --search invoice\n"
"  fsearch --cli --global --search invoice\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'file:size:>20mb'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'ext:jpg;png'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'path:projects report'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'report AND ext:pdf'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search '(draft OR final) !archive'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'file:regex:\".+\\.pdf$\"'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:AGENTS'        # case-sensitive\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:regex:\"^AGENTS\\.md$\"'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'glob:**/*.png'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'path:glob:**/AGENTS.md'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:glob:AGENTS.md' # case-sensitive glob\n"
"\n"
"Examples use space as AND. Try file:, folder:, path:, ext:, size:, dm:, "
"case:, regex:, and glob:.\n"
"Boolean syntax: AND or &&; OR or ||; NOT or !. Parentheses group terms.\n"
"Glob syntax: * excludes /; ** spans directories; ? matches one character; [a-"
"c] is a range;\n"
"Glob searches paths by default; use **/ for any depth; file:glob: searches "
"file names.\n"
"{png,jpg} selects alternatives; {01..12} is an inclusive numeric range; \\* "
"matches a literal *.\n"
msgstr ""
"Paggamit: fsearch --cli [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Hanapin ang umiiral na index ng FSearch at mga path na tumutugma sa pag-print.\n"
"\n"
"  -s, --search PATTERN       Maghanap gamit ang FSearch query syntax\n"
"      --path DIRECTORY        Paulit-ulit na maghanap sa ibaba ng DIRECTORY (default: kasalukuyang direktoryo)\n"
"      --global                Maghanap sa bawat na-index na lokasyon\n"
"      --limit COUNT          Mag-print ng hindi hihigit sa COUNT resulta\n"
"      --unlimit, --unlimited I-print ang bawat resulta\n"
"  -u, --update-database      I-scan muli ang na-configure na index at lumabas\n"
"      --about                Mag-print ng one-line build information\n"
"  -h, --help                 Ipakita ang tulong na ito\n"
"\n"
"Configuration: fsearch config --help\n"
"\n"
"Mga halimbawa:\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search invoice              # current directory\n"
"  fsearch --cli --path ~/Documents --search invoice\n"
"  fsearch --cli --global --search invoice\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'file:size:>20mb'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'ext:jpg;png'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'path:projects report'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'report AND ext:pdf'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search '(draft OR final) !archive'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'file:regex:\".+\\.pdf$\"'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:AGENTS'        # case-sensitive\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:regex:\"^AGENTS\\.md$\"'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'glob:**/*.png'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'path:glob:**/AGENTS.md'\n"
"  fsearch --cli --search 'case:glob:AGENTS.md' # case-sensitive glob\n"
"\n"
"Ang mga halimbawa ay gumagamit ng espasyo bilang AND. Subukan ang file:, folder:, path:, ext:, size:, dm:, case:, regex:, at glob:.\n"
"Boolean syntax: AT o &&; O o ||; HINDI o!. Mga termino ng pangkat ng panaklong.\n"
"Glob syntax: * hindi kasama ang /; ** sumasaklaw sa mga direktoryo; ? tumutugma sa isang karakter; [a-c] ay isang hanay;\n"
"Ang Glob ay naghahanap ng mga landas bilang default; gumamit ng **/ para sa anumang lalim; file:glob: naghahanap ng mga pangalan ng file.\n"
"Pinipili ng {png,jpg} ang mga alternatibo; {01..12} ay isang inclusive na hanay ng numero; \\* tumutugma sa isang literal na *.\n"

